  "target_response": {
    "text": "I do get stage data from your tracker — it's sensor-estimated rather than lab-grade, so treat the exact minutes loosely, but it's there. Last night it credited you 52 min of deep sleep out of 6.8 h total. Before judging the deep number, look at the total: your 6.8 h is about 0.6 h short of your 7.4 h need, and deep sleep is typically the stage that gets squeezed when the night runs short. So the honest read is less a deep-sleep problem than a duration problem wearing deep sleep as its symptom. One change to test: pull bedtime earlier by half an hour for a week and watch whether the estimated deep minutes rise with the longer nights. If the total normalizes and deep still looks thin, we dig further then.",
